1. Attribution.
   The above copyright notice and this permission notice (including the
   No Perdak Fire Condition below) shall be included in all copies or
   substantial portions of the Software.

2. No Perdak Fire Condition (the "NPF Condition").
   Permission to exercise ANY of the rights granted above -- including but
   not limited to using, reading, copying, modifying, merging, publishing,
   distributing, sublicensing, selling, or transferring the Software to any
   party anywhere -- is granted ONLY to a person whose perdak (also known as
   pukan) does not ignite ("catch fire") frequently, with or without cause.

   2.1 Definition of ignition.
       A person's perdak is deemed to be ON FIRE if such person exhibits
       disproportionate irritation, indignation, butthurt, or emotional
       combustion in response to matters including, but not limited to:

         (a) commits pushed without a Merge Request / Pull Request;
         (b) commits lacking a link to the corresponding Jira (or
             equivalent) issue;
         (c) force-pushes to shared branches;
         (d) any other petty grievance over which the person is prone
             to combust.

   2.2 Frequency and proportionality.
       Occasional, proportionate, and constructive frustration does NOT
       constitute ignition. This License targets only chronic and
       disproportionate perdak combustion, "for a reason and for no reason
       at all" (po povodu i bez).

   2.3 Automatic revocation.
       If a person's perdak is found to ignite frequently and
       disproportionately as described above, all rights granted under this
       Section 2 are immediately and automatically revoked with respect to
       that person. Any further action with the fork's modifications by that
       person constitutes infringement. (This does not affect the rights
       granted under Section 1 for the original MIT-licensed work.)

   2.4 Reinstatement (cooling-off).
       Rights revoked under Section 2.3 are automatically reinstated once,
       and for as long as, the person's perdak has verifiably cooled and
       remains non-combustible under normal operating conditions.

3. Determination.
   Determination of any person's perdak status under this Section 2 is made at
   the sole, final, and unappealable discretion of the copyright holder(s) of
   the modifications. Arguing loudly about this determination is itself
   admissible evidence of ignition.

